国际油价下跌和新冠疫情传播引发对全球经济的担忧，多国股市较年内高点跌幅超过20%，纷纷跌入“技术性熊市”。
Falling international oil prices and the spread of the new crown have raised concerns about the global economy, with multi-national stocks falling more than 20 per cent from their highs this year and falling into "techno-bear markets."
中国股市能否在疫情得到控制的情况下，真正走出独立行情，尚待进一步观察文|《财经》特派记者金焱发自华盛顿编辑| 苏琦在疫情恐惧和不确定性加大之际，全球金融市场连续上演“过山车行情”，悲观情绪弥漫。
Whether China's stock market can truly move out of isolation while the epidemic is under control remains to be seen. Yan Jin, a correspondent for Caijing, with editor and chief executive officer of Washington, D.C., at a time of heightened fear and uncertainty in global financial markets, is a source of pessimism.
而在疫情蔓延已经得到遏制的中国，沪深A股3月13日开盘后跌幅明显收窄。
And in China, where the epidemic has been contained, Shanghai and Shenzhen A shares fell sharply after the March 13 opening.
在澳大利亚、日本、巴西和意大利等国股市在3月跌入熊市后，美国在3月12日加入这一行列，当天美国三大股指收盘均跌入技术性熊市。
The U.S. joined the U.S. on March 12, after stocks tumbled into bear markets in Australia, Japan, Brazil and Italy in March, when all three indexes ended in a technical bear market.
与此同时，近来美国、泰国、菲律宾、韩国、巴基斯坦、印尼、巴西和加拿大股市股市都发生熔断。
Meanwhile, stock markets in the US, Thailand, the Philippines, South Korea, Pakistan, Indonesia, Brazil, and Canada have recently melted.
中国沪深A股3月13日低开跌幅近4%，港股恒生指数低开跌7%以上，随后均有所反弹，跌幅明显收窄，并未完全跟随美股走势。
Shares in Shanghai and Shenzhen fell nearly 4 per cent on March 13, while Hong Kong's Hang Seng index fell more than 7 per cent before rebounding markedly, narrowing sharply and not fully following US stock movements.
但在当天上午的沪港通和深港通交易中，北向资金延续了此前一天的净流出趋势明显。
But in the morning of the Shanghai-Hong Kong and Shenzhen-Hong Kong exchanges, the North to fund the continuation of the previous day's net outflow trend obvious.
3月12日美股大幅低开，标普500指数跌幅扩大至7%，触发本周第二次熔断，暂停交易15分钟。
U.S. stocks opened sharply lower on March 12, with the S & P 500 down 7%, triggering a second meltdown this week and suspending trading for 15 minutes.
恢复交易后，美股加速下跌，道指盘中从最低点反弹超过1000点后重拾跌势。
U. S. stocks accelerated after trading resumed, with the Dow rebounding more than 1, 000 points from its lowest point before falling again.
截止收盘，美国三大股指跌幅均超9%，道指收跌逾2300点，跌幅约10%，创1987年10月以来最大单日跌幅。
By the end of trading, the three main US stock indexes were down more than 9 per cent and the Dow was down more than 2,300 points, or about 10 per cent, the biggest one-day drop since October 1987.
标普500指数跌9.51%，纳指跌9.43%。
The S & P 500 was down 9.51% and the index was down 9.43%.
3月12日波音股价下跌15.4%，仅仅一个月时间，其市值就被腰斩。
Boeing shares fell 15.4 per cent on March 12 and were halved in value in just a month.
巴里克黄金跌10.2%，特斯拉跌9.4%。
Barrick fell 10.2 per cent and Tesla 9.4 per cent.
航空股重挫，美联航跌24.85%，达美航空跌21.02%，美国航空跌17.66%。
Airline stocks tumbled 24.85 percent, Delta Asia dropped 21.02 percent and American Airlines dropped 17.66 percent.
邮轮股抛售潮延续，皇家加勒比下跌31.78%，嘉年华下跌31.17%，挪威邮轮下跌35.62%。
Cruise sales continued, with the Royal Caribbean down 31.78 per cent, Carnival down 31.17 per cent and Norwegian cruise ship down 35.62 per cent.
一位华尔街分析师对《财经》记者说，过去几周市场的修正已完全把此前的乐观情绪转变为极端悲观主义。
A Wall Street analyst told Caijing that the market correction of the past few weeks has turned the optimism into extreme pessimism.
市场已连续处于超卖状态。
The market has been continuously oversold.
有分析认为，美股仅花了19天的时间便步入熊市，速度之快仅次于1931年的经济大萧条。
It took just 19 days for U.S. stocks to enter a bear market, analysts say, second only to the Great Depression of 1931.
1987年股灾，美股花了38天最终确认进入熊市，今年美股步入熊市的速度比当时快1倍。
In the 1987 crash, U.S. stocks took 38 days to finally confirm a bear market, and this year U.S. stocks entered a bear market twice as fast as then.
同时，对美国经济的担心也在加大。
Meanwhile, worries about the U. S. economy are mounting.
两党政策中心经济分析师威廉·霍格兰说：“我们估计这对美国来说可能是一个疲软的经济时期，我们不会看到我们预期的增长。
"We expect this to be a weak economic period for the United States and we won't see the growth we expect," said William Hoagland, economic analyst at the Center for Bipartisan Policy.
”越来越多的美国州和市政府宣布进入紧急状态。
More and more American states and municipalities are declaring states of emergency.
在一些城市领导者看来，世界似乎在短短几个小时内就发生了天翻地覆的变化。
For some city leaders, the world seems to have changed dramatically in just a few hours.
在美国华盛顿特区市长宣布华盛顿特区进入紧急状态后，当地时间3月12日下午，纽约市长白思豪宣布纽约市进入紧急状态，麦迪逊广场花园等大型场馆可能会关闭数月。
On the afternoon of March 12, New York City Governor Thomas Besho declared a state of emergency in New York City after the mayor of Washington, D.C., declared a state of emergency, and large venues such as Madison Square Gardens could be closed for months.
他预计下周该数字会上升至1000人。
He expects the figure to rise to 1,000 next week.
据悉，纽约市目前共有95例新冠肺炎病例，其中42例是在过去24小时中确诊的。
New York City now has 95 cases of new crown pneumonia, 42 of which have been diagnosed in the past 24 hours.
此外，捷克等国家也宣布全国进入紧急状态，以应对新冠肺炎疫情的暴发和蔓延。
In addition, countries such as the Czech Republic have declared a state of emergency in response to the outbreak and spread of pneumonia in the New Crown.
熔断与熊市美国疫情已出现越来越严重的迹象，它带来的不确定性让美国股市承压。
Meltdowns and bear markets There are growing signs of an American epidemic, and the uncertainty it brings is weighing on U.S. stocks.
多位投资者对《财经》记者表示，在过去11年间股市上涨了近四倍，是到了调整的时候了。
'Over the past 11 years, the stock market has nearly quadrupled, and it's time to adjust, 'several investors told Caijing.
对冲基金QQQ资本创始合伙人王洲对《财经》记者指出，这次股市暴跌之前的一年多的时间，股市进入某种自鸣得意的状态。
More than a year before the stock market crash, the stock market entered a sort of complacency, Wang Zhou, a founding partner of hedge fund QQQ Capital, told Caijing.
有数据显示，自特朗普政府上台到前段时间的市场巨震之前，美国股票大约上涨了近70%，而在这期间，即便是在美国企业盈利状况非常好的2018年，利润增长也不过刚刚达到两位数，更不要说一些年份企业盈利还出现了下降。
According to some data, US equities were up nearly 70% since the Trump administration took office until the recent market shock, and even in 2018, when US corporate profits were very good, profit growth was just double digits, not to mention some years of declining corporate profits.
疫情之下，美国金融市场终于显示出巨大的压力。
The financial markets of the United States are finally showing great pressure from the epidemic.
王洲指出，习惯了联储出手的市场就像个耍赖的小孩子，一不高兴就大哭大闹，等着联储伸出双手。
Wang Zhou pointed out that the market used to the Federal Reserve's hand is like a playful child who cries out when he is unhappy and waits for the Federal Reserve to extend its hands.
这次也不例外。
This time was no exception.
美联储在3月12日盘中宣布当日进行5000亿美元3个月期回购操作，并计划3月13日进行1次5000亿美元3个月期回购操作和1次5000亿美元的1个月回购操作。
The Federal Reserve announced on March 12 that it would conduct a $500bn three-month buy-back operation on the day, and a $500bn three-month buy-back operation and a $500bn one-month buy-back operation on March 13.
在新机制下，美联储将把购买范围扩大到“其他任何期限的国债”，包括票据、通胀保值债券TIPS和其他工具。
Under the new mechanism, the Fed would extend its purchases to "Treasury bonds of any other duration," including bills, TIPS, and other instruments.
纽约联储在声明中称，相关措施是为了应对因与冠状病毒爆发有关的债券融资市场极不寻常的混乱现象。
In a statement, the New York Fed said the measure was' in response to the highly unusual turmoil in the bond-financing market linked to the coronavirus outbreak.
美联储回购操作令美债收益率企稳，与利率关联密切的2年期美债收益率跌2.7个基点至0.460%，盘中最大触及0.360%，基准10年期美债收益率跌2.1个基点至0.801%，盘中最低触及0.636%，30年期美债收益率涨1.4个基点至1.455%。
The Fed buy-back stabilized yields on US debt, with the yield on two-year US debt closely linked to interest rates falling 2.7 basis points to 0.460 per cent, intraday maximum of 0.360 per cent, benchmark 10-year US Treasury yields down 2.1 basis points to 0.801 per cent, intraday lows of 0.636 per cent, and 30-year US Treasury yields up 1.4 basis points to 1.455 per cent.
市场动荡令投资者争相出售贵金属头寸以换取现金和流动性。
The market turmoil has seen investors scramble to sell precious metal positions in exchange for cash and liquidity.
纽约商品交易所4月交割的黄金期货价格重挫3.2%，收于1590.30美元/盎司，创2月28日以来收盘新低。
Gold futures on the New York Mercantile Exchange fell 3.2 per cent to $1590.30 an ounce, closing at a new low since February 28.
一边是美联储以激烈措施向银行体系注入更多流动性。
On one side is the Fed's drastic measures to inject more liquidity into the banking system.
一边是恐慌指数VIX突破70，创2008年金融危机以来新高。
On one side is a panic index of VIX surpassing 70, a new high since the 2008 financial crisis.
摩根大通指出，当基本面显示出改善迹象时市场才会企稳。
'The market stabilizes when fundamentals show signs of improvement, 'J.P. Morgan said.
在当前环境下，根本原因是公共卫生危机，而不是杠杆或盈利能力危机，因此需要等待疫情得到控制恐慌情绪才会改善。
Given the current environment, in which the underlying cause is a public-health crisis, rather than a crisis of leverage or profitability, there is a need to wait for the epidemic to be contained before fears can improve.
国际油价下跌和新冠疫情传播引发对全球经济的担忧，使多国股市较年内高点跌幅超过20%，纷纷跌入“技术性熊市”。
Falling international oil prices and the spread of the new crown have raised concerns about the global economy, sending multi-country stocks down more than 20 per cent from their highs this year and into a "technological bear market."
3月12日俄罗斯RTS开盘后延续前期走势大幅下挫，截至16:30当日跌幅已超7%，距离年内高点已经下跌近39%，位居全球各市场跌幅榜首位。
Russian RTS, which opened March 12, continued its early decline, falling more than 7 per cent on the day to 16: 30, down nearly 39 per cent from its peak this year and the world's biggest drop in markets.
紧随其后的还有希腊雅典ASE、比利时BFX等。
This was followed by ASE in Athens, Greece, and BFX in Belgium.
据统计显示，截至3月12日16:30，全球已有31个股票市场跌幅超20%，10个股票市场跌幅在15%-20%之间，而上证指数、深证成指的表现最为抗跌。
By 16: 30 on March 12, 31 stock markets had fallen more than 20 per cent, 10 had fallen between 15 per cent and 20 per cent, while the Shanghai index and the deep evidence index had been the most resilient.
新冠病毒疫情引起的全球风险资产暴跌加剧了印度的经济增长困境。
India's economic-growth woes have been exacerbated by the collapse of global risky assets caused by the new crown virus outbreak.
印度股市3月12日恢复跌势，主要股指接近跌入熊市，截至北京时间3月12日近午时，标普BSE Sensex指数大跌近5%，至33，932.5点。
India's stock market rallied on March 12, with major indexes close to a bear market, and the S & P BSE Sensex index fell nearly 5% to 33,932.5 in the late afternoon of March 12, Beijing time.
该指数已从1月14日的收盘高位下跌了19%，接近跌入熊市的20%门槛。
The index is down 19 per cent from its January 14 high and is close to the 20 per cent threshold for a bear market.
NSE Nifty 50指数下跌了4.5%。
The NSE Nifty 50 index is down 4.5%.
为阻止病毒传播，印度下令在4月15日之前暂停大部分签证。
To stop the virus from spreading, India has ordered most visas to be suspended until April 15.
这一决定是在美国总统特朗普宣布暂停从欧洲大陆到美国的旅游一个月之际作出的。
The decision comes a month after US President Donald Trump announced a moratorium on travel from continental Europe to the United States.
印度目前有60例新冠病毒确诊病例。
There are currently 60 confirmed cases of the new crown virus in India.
受全球新冠肺炎疫情蔓延影响，韩国综合股价指数3月12日大幅低开，盘中跌破1850点位后，一路下探至1808.56点，跌幅一度达到5%。
South Korea's composite index fell 5 percent to 1808.56 after plunging below 1,850 on March 12 as the global outbreak of pneumonia spread.
最终收盘报1834.33点，较前一交易日下跌73.94点，全天跌幅达3.87%。
The final closed at 1834.33, down 73.94 points, or 3.87%, from the previous day.
韩国创业板市场KOSDAQ收盘报563.49点，较前一交易日下跌32.12点。
Korea Growth Enterprise Market KOSDAQ closed at 563.49, down 32.12 points from the previous day.
韩国交易所当天下午在有价证券市场还启动了“临时停牌”措施，暂停程序交易五分钟。
South Korea's exchange that afternoon also launched a "temporary suspension" in the securities market, the suspension of procedures trading for five minutes.
这是韩国交易所时隔8年零5个月，再次在有价证券市场启动临时停牌措施。
This is the South Korean exchange after eight years and five months, once again in the securities market to initiate temporary suspension measures.
3月12日5点20分左右，据报道，巴基斯坦股指大跌，触发市场交易暂停机制。
At around 5.20 p.m. on March 12, it was reported that the Pakistan stock index had fallen sharply, triggering a suspension of trading in the market.
45分钟后恢复交易。
Trade resumes in 45 minutes.
当地时间3月11日巴西股市再次暴跌超过10%，一度触发熔断机制交易暂停。
Brazil's stock market plunged by more than 10% on March 11, 2006, triggering a temporary halt to trading in the fusing mechanism.
最终收于85171点，下跌7.64%。
It closed at 85171, down 7.64%.
公共卫生危机的阴影  随着新冠疫情在上百个国家蔓延，一场公共卫生危机袭卷全球。
A public health crisis looms over the world as the new crown epidemic spreads in hundreds of countries.
美国疾控中心主任罗伯特·雷德菲尔德3月10日在出席国会听证会时说，美国部分地区已经错过遏制疫情的机会窗口。
Robert Redfield, director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, told a congressional hearing on March 10 that parts of the United States had missed the window of opportunity to contain the outbreak.
多位美国公共卫生专家对《财经》记者指出，在疫情出现的早期更容易控制疫情，但美国联邦政府却错失了一系列机会，持续的延误使得疫情肆虐。
Many American public health experts told Caijing that it was easier to contain the outbreak in its early stages, but the federal government missed a series of opportunities, and continued delays caused the epidemic to fester.
美国疾病控制和预防中心主任罗伯特·雷德菲尔德3月11日说，美国存在新冠肺炎死亡病例被误认为是流感死亡病例的情况。
NEW YORK (Reuters) - Death from pneumonia has been mistaken for a flu death in the United States, director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, Robert Redfield, said Monday.
当天在美国国会众议院出席有关新冠肺炎疫情听证会时，有议员提问美国是否存在有些人看似死于流感，但实际上死于新冠肺炎的情况。
Speaking before the House of Representatives on the New Crown Pneumonia case, lawmakers asked if there were people in the United States who appeared to have died of the flu but died of pneumonia.
他回答说：“到目前为止，美国确实有一些病例是这样被诊断的。
"So far, a number of cases have been diagnosed in this way in the United States," he replied.
”根据美国疾控中心2月底发布的报告显示，今冬流感季美国估计已有至少3200万流感病例，其中1.8万人死于流感相关疾病。
According to a report released at the end of February by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, at least 32 million flu cases are estimated to have been reported in the United States this winter, of which 18,000 died from flu-related illnesses.
为了力挽狂澜，特朗普提出为受影响的行业和工人临时减税的想法。
To turn the tide, Trump has floated the idea of temporary tax cuts for affected industries and workers.
白宫也正在考虑为职工配备回家带薪假，但目前尚不清楚如何实施。
The White House is also considering giving its employees paid home leave, but it isn't clear how.
新的支出法案将需要国会民主党人的支持才能通过，民主党希望获得更多的资金用于医疗检测和护理，扩大失业保险以及增加对社会安全网项目的支出。
The new spending bill will require congressional Democrats, who want more money for medical testing and care, expanded unemployment insurance and increased spending on social safety net programs.
两党政策中心经济分析师霍格兰说：“这将在短期内增加联邦赤字，但是如果这意味着保护美国公众的安全和保障、恢复发展所需要的经济信心，那也是值得的。
"It would increase the federal deficit in the short term, but it would also be worth it if it meant protecting the safety and security of the American public and restoring the economic confidence needed for development," said John Hoagland, an economic analyst at the Center for Bipartisan Policy.
”在政府依然踌躇如何快速遏制疫情之际，疫情打倒了好莱坞著名影星汤姆·汉克斯夫妇、明星运动员，促使NBA宣布本赛季停赛；另外美国国会确诊首例病例，多名议员进行自我隔离。
While the government still hesitates to contain the epidemic quickly, the outbreak brought down the famous Hollywood movie star Tom and Mrs. Hanks and star athletes, prompting the NBA to suspend its season, and the first case confirmed by the United States Congress, with many members of Congress isolating themselves.
当地时间3月12日，为避免人员聚集加剧新冠病毒传播风险，美国迪士尼官方宣布即日起到3月底，临时关闭位于加利福尼亚州安纳海姆的迪士尼乐园。
Disney officials announced the temporary closure of Disneyland in Anaheim, Calif., until the end of March to avoid a build-up that would exacerbate the risk of spreading the virus.
除了这次因疫情影响关闭乐园，加州迪斯尼乐园在历史上仅经历过三次暂停营业，分别是911恐怖袭击、肯尼迪总统遇刺、1994年洛杉矶北岭地震。
In addition to closing the park because of the epidemic, California Disneyland has been suspended only three times in its history, the terrorist attacks of September 11, the assassination of President Kennedy, and the 1994 Los Angeles North Ridge earthquake.
目前迪斯尼没公布是否计划关闭其在佛罗里达州的迪斯尼乐园。
Disney has not announced plans to close its Disneyland in Florida.
新冠肺炎疫情的不断加剧，促使美国首都华盛顿特区宣布进入紧急状态。
The worsening outbreak of New Crown Pneumonia has prompted a state of emergency in Washington, D.C.
随后纽约市宣布进入紧急状态。
The city then declared a state of emergency.
截至目前，美国累计1,322宗确诊个案，死亡人数38人，其中纽约市的确诊个案共95宗。
To date, there have been 1,322 confirmed cases with 38 deaths in the United States, 95 of which have been confirmed in New York City.
美国多个地方都已进入紧急状态。
A state of emergency has been imposed in many parts of the United States.
欧洲被称为疫情的新震中。
Europe is called the new epicentre of the epidemic.
意大利全国6048万人都在封锁中，非紧急状况不得外出。
In Italy, 60.48 million people are under blockade and must not go out without an emergency.
所有婚丧喜庆和运动赛事，宗教活动通通不能办。
All weddings, festivities and sports events cannot be attended by all religious activities.
除了药局和超市其他店家全数关闭。
All the stores except the pharmacy and the supermarket are closed.
截至当地时间3月12日下午15点，捷克新冠病毒感染病例已达96例，全国13个州和首都布拉格无一幸免，大部分患者集中在布拉格。
By 15: 00 p.m. local time on March 12, the Czech Republic had 96 new cases of infection, with 13 states and the capital, Prague, mostly concentrated.
当地时间3月12日，捷克总理巴比什和第一副总理兼内务部长哈马切克召开新闻发布会，宣布全国进入紧急状态，以应对新冠肺炎疫情在该国的暴发和蔓延。
On 12 March local time, Czech Prime Minister Babish and First Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of the Interior Hama _ ek held a press conference to declare a national state of emergency in response to the outbreak and spread of the New Crown Pneumonia epidemic in the country.
紧急状态从3月12日下午14点开始，为期30天。
The state of emergency began at 14 p.m. on 12 March for a period of 30 days.
在紧急状态下，自3月14日开始，禁止包括伊朗、意大利、韩国、德国、西班牙等15个国家的公民入境捷克，同时禁止捷克公民前往。
During the state of emergency, citizens of 15 countries, including Iran, Italy, the Republic of Korea, Germany and Spain, were prohibited from entering the Czech Republic as from 14 March, while Czech citizens were prohibited from travelling.
(拥有长期居留卡，或超过90天的短期居留卡的人除外)；自3月13日午夜开始实行边境管控，捷克与德国和奥地利的边界只开放11个过境点。
(Excluding persons with long-term residence cards or short-term residence cards exceeding 90 days); border controls have been in place since midnight on 13 March, and only 11 border crossings between the Czech Republic and Germany and Austria have been opened.
调动军队将前往捷克与德、奥边境，协助警察检查所有过境旅客，对疑似感染者进行隔离。
The troops will travel to the Czech border with Germany and Austria to help police check all transit passengers and isolate suspected infections.
外国公民将不允许通过德国和奥地利的边境进入捷克。
Foreign citizens will not be allowed to enter the Czech Republic through the German-Austrian border.
停止签发一切签证和超过90天的居留许可，直至另行通知。
All visas and residence permits exceeding 90 days will be suspended until further notice.
自3月13日开始，酒吧和餐馆不得在晚上20点至早上6点之间营业。
Since March 13, bars and restaurants are not allowed to open between 20pm and 6am.
自3月13日早上6点开始，关闭健身房、游泳馆及其他体育设施；关闭俱乐部、美术馆、图书馆、5000平米以上的商场里的餐饮场所；禁止30人以上的活动(不适用于政府机构的会议等)。
From 6 a.m. on 13 March, gymnasiums, swimming pools and other sports facilities were closed; clubs, galleries, libraries, catering establishments in shopping malls of more than 5,000 m2 were closed, and activities of more than 30 persons (not applicable to meetings of government agencies, etc.) were prohibited.
何时取消将另行通知。
Cancellation will be announced.
